        "sample": [
          {
            "x4_code": null,
            "free_txt": [
              "The 7Be target was fabricated using 7Be chemically",
              "extracted from the cooling water of the SINQ facility",
              "at PSI. After mass separation the 7Be ion beam was",
              "focused loss free through a 5 mm diameter diaphragm and",
              "implanted into a 1.5 um thin Al foil. The beam spot had",
              "about 3 mm diameter. This Al foil was mounted between",
              "two 1.5 mm thick Al frames, with the external",
              "dimensions of 112 x 50.5 mm2.",
              "6LiF standard was supplied by the Institute for",
              "Reference Materials Measurements (IRMM) Geel. The",
              "standard sample was prepared by magnetron sputtering as",
              "a 6LiF homogeneous layer with a thickness of 30.2(2)",
              "um/cm2 deposited on a 1.5 um Al foil.",
              "The targets were tilted by 15 degree with respect to",
              "the neutron beam plane.",
              "An eight-day measurement with 7Be and a three-day",
              "measurement with 6LiF with a delimited area of 11 mm in",
              "diameter were combined.",
              "The 7Be sample and the 6LiF standard were irradiated",
              "with a collimated thermal neutron beam in a large",
              "vacuum chamber."
            ]
          }
        ],
